CREATING AN EC2 INSTANCE.

- search for ec2 in the search menu.
- in the network section create a keypair tonuse in decrypting the password to log into the ec2 instance.
- Click on Launch Instance and then select Launch instance from the drop down.
- Add a desired name i.e [Your Initials] Windows Web Server
- Select t2.medium in Instance Type.
- Select the key pair that you created in the beginning of this lab from the drop-down.
- In the Network settings section, configure the security group to Allow RDP and HTTP from the internet.
- Expand the Advanced Details tab at the bottom of the screen and enter the following values in the User data field. For all other choices accept the default values. 
- input the user data script.
- Verify your selections are correct and then choose Launch instance.